          "source_kind": "tzx-html",
          "source_html": "<div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>Questions 27 - 32</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Choose the correct answer.</span></p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">27</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>In the first paragraph, what did the children in the experiment have to do?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> spot the differences between a real room and a smaller version</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> make a copy of a life-sized room using small furniture</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> hide a large toy in a tiny room</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_27\" id=\"opt_27_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q27\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_27_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> locate a toy in a life-sized room</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> D. locate a toy in a life-sized room</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问的是在第一个段落的实验中孩子们需要做什么。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“the first paragraph”和“children”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：A段，“we then encouraged the child to find &#39;Big Snoopy&#39;, a large version of the toy &#39;hiding in the same place in his big room.&#39;”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：根据原文内容，孩子们需要在真实房间（life-sized room）中找到一个藏起来的玩具。因此正确答案是D。<br/></p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：原文中的“find”对应选项中的“locate”。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">28</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>What was the result of the first experiment?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> Both two-and-a-half-and three-year-olds completed the task successfully.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> Three-year-olds could mentally relate the two rooms they had been shown.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> Two-and-a-half-year-olds could relate more closely to the toys as symbols.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_28\" id=\"opt_28_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q28\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_28_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> Two-and-a-half-year-olds had poorer memory than three-year-olds.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. Three-year-olds could mentally relate the two rooms they had been shown.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问的是第一个实验的结果。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“first experiment”、“two-and-a-half-year-olds”、“three-year-olds”和“result”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：B段，“The three-year-olds were very successful. After they observed the small toy being placed behind the miniature couch, they ran into the room and found the large toy behind the real couch. But the two-and-a-half-year-olds failed abysmally.”这句话表明三岁的小孩能够成功地理解两个房间之间的关系，并找到大狗玩具。</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：三岁孩子能够成功找到玩具，而两岁半的孩子则无法关联两个房间，说明三岁孩子能理解模型与现实房间的关系，并成功找到大玩具。因此答案是B。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">29</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>In the fourth paragraph, what does the writer say about children and pictures?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> Infants are unable to understand that pictures serve a double purpose.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> Young children may understand pictures more readily than adults.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> Infants can understand that a picture of food cannot be eaten.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_29\" id=\"opt_29_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q29\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_29_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> Adults should encourage children to look at pictures from an early age.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. Infants are unable to understand that pictures serve a double purpose.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问的是作者在第四段中对孩子和图片的看法。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“the fourth paragraph”和“children and pictures”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：D段，“The problem stems from the duality inherent in all symbolic objects: they are real in themselves and also representations of something else.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：原文中提到孩子无法理解图片的双重性质，即图片既是一个真实的物体，又是另一个事物的象征或代表。因此答案是A。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">30</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>In the third experiment, what did the writer notice about the reactions of the toddlers?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> They often behaved in an unpredictable way.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> They were only comfortable performing very familiar tasks.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> They became frustrated when they could not achieve a task.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_30\" id=\"opt_30_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q30\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_30_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> They behaved the same whether they were successful or not.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> D. They behaved the same whether they were successful or not.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问的是作者在第三个实验中注意到了什么。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“the third experiment”和“reactions”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：G段提到“Interestingly, most of the children showed little or no reaction to their failed attempts.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：根据原文，在G段中，作者描述了实验中幼儿尝试使用缩小版的物品（如滑梯和汽车）执行与之前使用正常大小的物品相同的动作，但失败了。原文明确指出，这里明确说明大多数幼儿对他们失败的尝试没有表现出反应，或者说反应很少。因此他们的行为一致，无论是成功还是失败，他们的反应几乎没有变化。因此答案是D。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">31</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>What did the experiment involving a mathematical problem suggest about children&#39;s learning?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> Children are able to understand complex concepts at an early age.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> Children younger than seven cannot learn using pencil and paper alone.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> Using blocks can make it harder for children to learn new concepts.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_31\" id=\"opt_31_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q31\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_31_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> Teachers should try using blocks to teach mathematics to lower level students.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. Using blocks can make it harder for children to learn new concepts.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问的是关于数学问题的实验对孩子学习的启示。</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“mathematical problem”和“children&#39;s learning”</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：H段提到“<span style=\"font-family: Arial;\">We taught an identical comparison group the same concept, but using pencil and paper. Both groups learned to solve the problems equally well, but the group using blocks took three times as long to do so.</span>”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：H段提到，实验中有两组孩子，一组使用积木，另一组使用纸和铅笔。结果表明，两组在解决问题上学得同样好，但使用积木的那组花了三倍的时间。原文显示，使用积木并没有帮助孩子更快地理解概念，反而延长了学习时间。因此答案是C。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">32</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>What does Deloache conclude about the results of her and Chong&#39;s experiment?</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_32\" id=\"opt_32_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_32_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> Children's books should be more interactive.\r\n</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_32\" id=\"opt_32_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_32_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> 2-D books should contain realistic images.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_32\" id=\"opt_32_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_32_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> Simpler books may be better learning tools.</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_32\" id=\"opt_32_D\" data-zyz-question=\"q32\" value=\"D\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_32_D\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>D.</strong> 3-D books help weaker students to progress.</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. Simpler books may be better learning tools.</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问Deloache对于他和Chong的实验结果的结论。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位信息：Deloache, Chong&#39;s experiment<br/></p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：I段，Accordingly, we used different types of books to teach letters to 30-month-old children. One was a simple old-fashioned alphabet book with each letter accompanied by an appropriate picture. The other was a 3-D version. The children using the traditional book subsequently recognised more letters than those using the 3-D book.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：原文提到使用传统字母书教学时，孩子认识的字母比使用3D书教学时更多。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><strong>Questions 33 - 35</strong></p><p><br/></p><p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending. Choose the correct ending and move it into the gap.</p></div>\r\n    <div class=\"word-bank-container\">\r\n        <div class=\"wb-title\">Options (Word Bank):</div>\r\n        <div class=\"wb-grid\">\r\n            <div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>A.</strong> that a three-year-old may still expect an image to perform a real task.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>B.</strong> how quickly children can learn the alphabet. </div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>C.</strong> the best age for children to begin school.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>D.</strong> the effectiveness of symbolic objects as teaching tools.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>E.</strong> whether young children are puzzled by pictures.</div><div class=\"wb-item\"><strong>F.</strong> that young children expect tiny objects to function in the same way as life-sized ones.</div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    \r\n    <div class=\"matrix-container\">\r\n        <table>\r\n            <thead><tr><th class=\"corner-header\">Question / Paragraph</th><th>A</th><th>B</th><th>C</th><th>D</th><th>E</th><th>F</th></tr></thead>\r\n            <tbody>\r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">33</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p><strong>33 </strong>The test involving 9-month-old babies attempted to find out <span class=\"input-blank\">________</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_33\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_33\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_33\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_33\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_33\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_33\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q33\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"7\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：E</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是关于9个月大的婴儿的实验试图了解什么。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“9-month-old babies”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：E段提到“We began testing infants&#39; understanding of pictures by putting a book of highly realistic colour photographs of individual objects in front of nine-month-olds. To our surprise, every child in the study reached out to feel or scratch the pictures.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：这段文字解释了对9个月大的婴儿进行的测试，旨在发现婴儿是否困惑于图片以及图片与实际物体的区别。婴儿伸手去摸图片，因为他们还不理解图片的双重性质。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">34</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p><strong>34</strong> The third experiment revealed <span class=\"input-blank\">________</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_34\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_34\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_34\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_34\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_34\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_34\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q34\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"7\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：F</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是第三个实验揭示了什么。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“third experiment”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：G段提到“Most children attempted to perform the same actions with the miniature items that they had with the larger ones.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：第三次实验中，研究人员发现孩子们期望微型物体能像大型物体一样正常工作。他们试图坐在微型椅子上或爬进微型汽车里，虽然这些微型物品实际上无法承载他们的行为。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">35</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p><strong>35</strong> The maths experiment was designed to assess <span class=\"input-blank\">________</span></p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_35\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_35\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_35\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_35\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_35\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55329_35\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q35\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"7\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：D</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是数学实验的设计目的是什么。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“maths experiment”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：H段，“Teachers everywhere use blocks or other objects to represent numerical quantity. However, if young children do not understand the relation between an object and what it represents, this could be counterproductive. To demonstrate this, we taught six-and seven-year-olds a difficult subtraction problem using blocks.”&nbsp;<br/></p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：在H段中，作者提到教师使用积木等物体来表示数字数量，实验旨在评估象征性物体（如积木）作为教学工具的有效性。虽然使用积木的学生能够解决问题，但所需时间是使用纸笔学生的三倍，说明象征性物体的教学效果可能并不如预期。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>Questions 36 - 40</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Choose </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>YES</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose</span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong> NO </strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or choose </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</span></p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">36</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The results of the first experiment revealed unexpected information.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_36\" id=\"opt_36_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q36\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_36_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. YES</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问第一个实验的结果是否揭示了意想不到的信息。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“first experiment”和“unexpected information”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：A段提到“About 20 years ago I had one of those wonderful moments when research takes an unexpected but fruitful turn.&quot;C段提到“I realised my memory study was instead a study of symbolic understanding... the children&#39;s failure might be telling us something about how and when children acquire the ability to understand that one object stands for another.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：原文明确表示，研究人员原本计划研究记忆，但通过实验，意外地发现了关于儿童符号理解的知识。这是他们之前没有预料到的。因此答案是YES。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">37</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Infants react the same way to both drawings and photographs.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_37\" id=\"opt_37_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q37\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_37_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. NO</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问婴儿是否对绘画和照片的反应相同。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：关键词是“Infants”和“drawings and photographs”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：E段提到“However, when depicted objects bear little resemblance to the real thing – as in a black and white drawing – infants rarely explore them.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：原文明确指出婴儿对照片和绘画的反应不同：他们更倾向于探索照片，而很少对黑白绘画表现出兴趣。因此，婴儿不会以相同方式对待绘画和照片，因此答案是NO。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">38</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Toddlers are used to failing in many of the tasks they try to perform.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_38\" id=\"opt_38_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q38\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_38_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> A. YES</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问幼儿是否习惯于在许多任务中失败。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“toddlers”和“failing”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：G段提到“We think this probably reflects the fact that toddlers&#39; daily lives are full of unsuccessful attempts to do one thing or another.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：原文表明幼儿经常面对失败的任务，因此他们对这些失败已经习以为常。幼儿的生活中充满了失败的尝试，因此答案是YES。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">39</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>The confusion of symbols and real objects has little significance for educational practice.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_39\" id=\"opt_39_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q39\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_39_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> B. NO</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问符号和实物的混淆对教育实践是否没有什么意义。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“confusion”和“symbols and real objects”和“educational practice”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：G段提到“This confusion has implications for educational practice.”以及“Teachers everywhere use blocks or other objects to represent numerical quantity. However, if young children do not understand the relation between an object and what it represents, this could be counterproductive.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：符号和实物的混淆对教育实践有重要影响，并进一步解释了为什么这种混淆对教育实践有意义：如果孩子不理解符号和实际对象的关系，教学效果可能会适得其反，说明这对教育实践有重要的影响。因此答案是NO。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div><div class=\"big-section\">\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">40</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p><strong>Children enjoy reading 3D books more than 2D books.</strong></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <div class=\"opt-list\" style=\"margin:10px 0 10px 25px;\">\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_A\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"A\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_A\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>A.</strong> YES</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_B\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"B\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_B\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>B.</strong> NO</label>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div style=\"margin-bottom:5px;\">\r\n            <input type=\"radio\" name=\"radio_40\" id=\"opt_40_C\" data-zyz-question=\"q40\" value=\"C\">\r\n            <label for=\"opt_40_C\" style=\"cursor:pointer;\"><strong>C.</strong> NOT GIVEN</label>\r\n        </div></div>\r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> C. NOT GIVEN</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\"><p>审题：题目问孩子是否更喜欢阅读3D书籍。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：关键词是“Children”、“3D books”和“2D books”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：I段提到“... children using the traditional book subsequently recognised more letters than those using the 3D book.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：原文I段和J段讨论了3D书和2D书的学习效果差异，但没有提到儿童是否更喜欢阅读3D书。因此答案是NOT GIVEN。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div>",
